sudo - Super user do!
su - super user
sudo passwd root (in ubuntu let us set password for root)
PATH=$PATH:/usr/sbin:/sbin  (Setting path variable to look for executables)
The tilde (~) is a Linux "shortcut" to denote a user's home directory. Thus tilde slash (~/) is the beginning of a path to a file or directory below the user's home directory. 
For example, for user01, file /home/user01/test. file can also be denoted by ~/test.
Alt-F2 run command window
Shift + Ctrl-T (opens a terminal in a new tab)
